      "message": "I think maintaining a table like this manually is not a sustainable solution. \n\nI\u0027d propose we build a script generating a table like this from gerrit REST API and data available on gerrit-ci. Then we could add a build job regenerating the page e.g. once a day. Or we enhance gitiles project display to do this dynamically.\n\nWe can get a flat list of all plugins like this\ncurl \"https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/a/projects/?p\u003dplugins%2F\u0026format\u003dTEXT\" [1]\n\nThe project description is stored in its project.config on the refs/meta/config branch, that\u0027s also feeding the description shown in gitiles [3].\n\nWe can test existence of branches using the get branch REST API [4] or list all branches using [5].\n\nUsing a query like [6] we can get all jenkins jobs and their last build timestamp and status, with a little pattern matching we can find the relevant jobs and match them with the list of plugins we got from Gerrit REST API\n\nWDYT ?\n\n[1] https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/Documentation/rest-api-projects.html#suggest-projects\n[2] I have no access to refs/meta/config on googlesource\n[3] https://gerrit.googlesource.com/plugins/\n[4] https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/Documentation/rest-api-projects.html#get-branch\n[5] https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/Documentation/rest-api-projects.html#list-branches\n[6] https://gerrit-ci.gerritforge.com/api/json?pretty\u003dtrue\u0026tree\u003djobs[name,lastBuild[timestamp,result]]\nfound in https://www.cloudbees.com/blog/taming-jenkins-json-api-depth-and-tree",
